## Special Case -------------------------------
### Generated JS scope isolation
  Generated files in `./static/generated/CustomBlocks` and `./static/generated/Generators` are loaded sequentially in the browser.
  Do not use shared top-level variable names across files (e.g. `const BLOCKS`) in global scope.
  Each generated file must isolate its scope (e.g. wrap file content in IIFE) to avoid redeclaration errors.
  If redeclaration happens, only the first-loaded category may work and other category items will not be shown.
### options
  If a item has options, use dropdown menu.
  If a item has no options, use input box.
  If an option has `description`, show it when dropdown menu is opened and mouse is over that option item.
  If an option includes `parameters`, show those additional parameters in the block.
  Additional parameters by option are supported only for 1 depth.
  Nested option-parameters under those additional parameters are ignored.
### Function block to Behavior Tree
  Scenario file is saved in Blockly workspace JSON format.
  Clicking `Behavior Tree` converts current Blockly workspace to Behavior Tree JSON.
  Function call block (`procedures_callnoreturn`) is converted to:
    `{ "type": "Subtree", "id": "XXXXXXXX" }`
  `id` is the function name (`fields.NAME` / function name state).
  Behavior Tree top-level object uses parent keys:
    - `Root`
    - function ids (function names)
  Each function key value format:
    `"XXXXXXXX": { "child": { ... } }`
  If function body is already a single `Sequence`, do not wrap it with another `Sequence`.
  In Graphical Tree, render `Root` and each function id as separate trees.
### Reference Action Block
  If action has `BRIC.XXXX:` prefix, treat it as a reference action block.
  In Behavior Tree JSON view and Graphical Tree view, do not display the prefix part.
  Show/display action only with the part after `:`.
  On `Export`, preprocess this action:
    - Reference file is `./btInfo/XXXX.json`.
    - Find matching entry by `parameter.name`.
    - Replace node `parameter` with matched `data`.
    - Replace node `action` with the action text after `:`.
### Sound id
  Default value of `id` in `Sound` category is `2000`.
  For blocks in `Sound` category whose action name includes `start_play`, increase `id` for each new block.
  If all such `start_play` blocks are removed, reset the next `id` value to the default `2000`.
### min max
  If a item has only one of min or max, use input box and use it as default value.
  If a item has min, use dropdown menu.
  If parameter type is float and both min and max exist, create dropdown options with 20 steps (inclusive).
  Example: min=0, max=1 -> 0.00, 0.05, 0.10, ... , 1.00
### description
#### Description for a block
  Add a question icon on the left side of a block only if 'description' exists and is not empty.
  If there is no 'description' or it is empty, hide the question icon.
  Clicking the question icon shows the 'description' in a popup UI.
  Do not use browser alert window for help message.
#### Description for parameters
  Add a question icon before each parameter.
  Clicking parameter question icon shows its description in the same popup UI.
#### Question icon
   Circle icon include '?' in the center of the circle.
   Background color is blue, the '?' color is white.
   The circle has a thin white outline.
#### Help popup UI
  Help popup is a custom UI box, not browser default tooltip.
  Popup has a text box and a pointer tail (upside-down triangle).
  Frame color follows the source block color.
  Text box uses light yellow background.
  There should be no visible line between the text box and pointer tail.
  `Function` category help popup can keep its own frame thickness.
## Default value -------------------------------
   If there is no min or max value for a default value, set the value below according to it's type.
### float: 0.0
### int: 0
### string: empty string.
